definition.value: A phosphatidylethanolamine in which the amino group is dimethylated.
An aldehyde that consists of ethane bearing a formyl substituent. The parent of the class of propanals.
A pyridinecarboxamide that is pyridine in which the hydrogen at position 3 is replaced by a carboxamide group.
Any glycosyloxyflavone that consists of a flavonol attached to a 6-O-malonyl-beta-D-glucosyl residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage.
A derivative of scyllo-inositol where the 1- and 3-hydroxy groups are replaced by guanidino and amino groups respectively.
